            "Plate": "14 of 18",
            "Location": "Northern Coast",
            "Year": "2024",
            "Process": "Silver gelatin print",
            "Edition": "1 / 25"
          },
          "body": "Plate 14 was made on the second-to-last morning of the four-month working period. The window faced north, the air was unusually still, and the photograph required no second exposure. It is the longest single contemplation of a single object in the working archive."
        },
        {
          "runninghead": "MONOGRAPH NO. 07 · MAYA HALDEN · SURFACE",
          "eyebrow": "— PLATE 22",
          "title": "Surface",
