          "caption_2": "Photographed at Place des Vosges, the third week of February, the wettest in eleven years.",
          "folio": "p. 38"
        },
        {
          "label": "REYKJAVIK",
          "caption": "Northernmost capital of any sovereign state; pop. 130,000; founded by Norse settlers in 874; latitude 64°N.",
          "caption_2": "Photographed from the harbour at twenty past ten on a December morning, sun barely above the horizon.",
          "folio": "p. 46"
        },
        {
          "label": "BUENOS",
          "caption": "Pop. 3.12m metropolitan area 15.4m; founded twice — 1536 and 1580; capital of Argentina since the third of May 1853.",
          "caption_2": "Photographed at San Telmo on a Sunday afternoon, the antiques market half-folded by the rain.",
          "folio": "p. 54"
        },
        {
          "label": "MUMBAI",
          "caption": "Pop. 21m metropolitan area; original archipelago of seven islands joined by reclamation between 1782 and 1845.",
          "caption_2": "Photographed at Marine Drive at six in the morning, in light that lasted twelve minutes.",
          "folio": "p. 62"
        },
        {
          "label": "ISTANBUL",
          "caption": "The only city to span two continents; pop. 15.8m; founded as Byzantium in 657 BCE; renamed Istanbul in 1930.",
          "caption_2": "Photographed from a ferry crossing the Bosphorus at half past five on a Sunday in late September.",
          "folio": "p. 70"
        },
        {
          "label": "HONG KONG",
          "caption": "Pop. 7.5m on 1,106 km²; one of the most densely settled places in the world; over 1,500 high-rises.",
          "caption_2": "Photographed at Victoria Peak forty minutes before sunset, the third clear evening of the visit.",
          "folio": "p. 78"
        }
      ],
