      "dedicated_sets": [
        {
          "label": "KYOTO",
          "folio": "p. 06",
          "caption": "Photographed at Kiyomizu-dera in the half-hour before the morning gates opened, the third Wednesday of November. The temple steps had been swept; the morning fog had not yet lifted; two priests in ceremonial dress crossed the courtyard from the southern entrance."
        },
        {
          "label": "PARIS",
          "folio": "p. 14",
          "caption": "Photographed at Place des Vosges on the third morning of the visit, in light the photographer described as adequate. The arcade was empty. A dog, off the leash, had been crossing the square in slow circles for seven minutes before the exposure, by which point the dog was the subject."
        },
        {
          "label": "ROME",
          "folio": "p. 22",
          "caption": "Photographed in Trastevere, on the corner of vicolo del Cinque, the morning after the storm. The pavement was wet. A café owner had begun setting up the chairs for the day. Two cats, neither of them his, had taken up the same positions as on every previous morning."
        },
        {
          "label": "ISTANBUL",
          "folio": "p. 30",
          "caption": "Photographed from a ferry crossing the Bosphorus, the sixth visit of the year, in autumn light that did not last appreciably longer than the crossing. Two fishermen on the stern had been fishing without luck for two hours when the fourth and final exposure was made."
        },
        {
          "label": "BARCELONA",
          "folio": "p. 38",
          "caption": "Photographed at the corner of carrer de Mallorca with passeig de Gràcia, in morning light that did not appreciably differ from the previous visit, three years prior. A tour group of twelve had paused at the corner; the guide, in English, was explaining the architecture."
        },
        {
          "label": "AMSTERDAM",
          "folio": "p. 46",
          "caption": "Photographed at the Singel canal, on the morning of the second day, in conditions approximating those of the photographer's first visit, seven years prior. A houseboat moored against the east bank had been repainted. The bicycles chained to the railing had not changed."
        },
        {
          "label": "VIENNA",
          "folio": "p. 54",
          "caption": "Photographed at Café Hawelka on the third morning of the visit, in light the photographer described as the best of the trip. The same waiter who had served the photographer eleven years prior remembered the order, which is the principal documentary observation."
        },
        {
          "label": "CAIRO",
          "folio": "p. 62",
          "caption": "Photographed in the Khan el-Khalili bazaar, on the morning of the sixth day, in light that did not appreciably reach the ground. A coppersmith, visible at the frame's right edge, had been working on the same teapot for two hours when the exposure was made."
        },
        {
          "label": "JERUSALEM",
          "folio": "p. 70",
          "caption": "Photographed at the Western Wall on the morning of the second day, in conditions the photographer described as adequate. The square had been sparsely populated for twenty minutes before the exposure; a group of schoolchildren was slowly dispersing into the old city."
        },
        {
          "label": "DONOSTIA",
          "folio": "p. 78",
          "caption": "Photographed at the Concha bay on the morning of the third day, in light the photographer described as the strongest argument for returning. The tide was out. Two surfers had been in the water since before the exposure, and were still in the water at the end of the hour."
        }
      ],
      "content_theme": {
        "primary": "dedicated",
        "mode": "dedicated_per_template"
      }
    },
