          "runninghead": "MONOGRAPH NO. 04 · ROBERT WILLIAM · A QUIET LIGHT — FULL ARCHIVE EDITION",
          "title": "A Quiet Light",
          "folio": "p. 22",
          "body": "This is the full archive edition of Robert William's A QUIET LIGHT, prepared by the publisher in collaboration with the photographer's working studio. The four plates reproduced in this monograph are working representative selections from the eighteen-frame final portfolio, chosen by the working editor on the basis of working completeness and working chronological span.",
          "body_2": "William has, in the working introduction prepared for this edition, indicated that the four working plates are not necessarily the four he would have chosen himself. The working editor's working selection is, in his working note, accepted with the working caveat that the working monograph is not, in any working sense, a definitive reading of the working portfolio.",
          "infobox": {
            "Photographer": "Robert William",
            "Born": "1971, Edinburgh",
            "Series": "A Quiet Light",
            "Working Period": "4 months · spring–summer",
            "Plates": "18 final / 412 working",
            "Format": "Medium format · Mamiya 7",
            "Film": "Kodak Portra 400",
            "Edition": "1 / 25, signed",
            "First Showing": "Autumn exhibition, north gallery"
          }
        },
        {
          "runninghead": "MONOGRAPH NO. 07 · MAYA HALDEN · SURFACE — FULL ARCHIVE EDITION",
          "title": "Surface",
          "folio": "p. 30",
          "body": "This is the full archive edition of Maya Halden's SURFACE, prepared in collaboration with the working studio in Reykjavik. The four plates reproduced are working representative selections from the forty-frame final portfolio, chosen by the working editor on the basis of working diversity of working subject material across the working calendar year.",
          "body_2": "Halden has, in the working note prepared for this edition, indicated that the working selection is the working editor's, and that her working preference would have been a different working four plates, sequenced by working light direction. The working editor's working choice is accepted, in her working note, with the working acknowledgement that the working monograph is one of several working possible readings.",
          "infobox": {
            "Photographer": "Maya Halden",
            "Born": "1984, Reykjavik",
            "Series": "Surface",
