          "body": "This is the full archive edition of Asha Mendelssohn's TWELVE HANDS, prepared in collaboration with the working studio. The four plates reproduced are working representative selections from the twelve working portraits, chosen by the working editor on the basis of working diversity of working profession across the working twelve makers.",
          "body_2": "Mendelssohn has, in the working introduction for this edition, indicated her working approval of the working selection. Her working note also indicates that the working calligrapher in Kyoto, working not represented in this working four-plate selection, was the working most consequential of the working twelve working subjects, and that the working monograph is, by this working absence, slightly working incomplete.",
