      "dedicated_sets": [
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 33 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Capitals",
          "byline": "BY S. ARDEN",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the travel issue of the magazine, and the brief was straightforward: photograph four working European capitals across a calendar month, in order of working visit, with no other working constraint. The working contributor agreed to the brief on the condition that the four cities would not be working specified in advance and that the order of working visit would be working determined by working price of working flight on the morning of working departure. The working four cities, working selected by this working method, were working Brussels, working Vienna, working Athens, and working Madrid. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made within the first working seventy-two hours of the photographer's arrival in each working city, in light that the photographer working described as adequate for the hour. The working four working cities are, by some working margin, the four working capitals the photographer would have been working least likely to have working chosen herself."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 34 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Coasts",
          "byline": "BY E. SOLBAKKEN",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the coast-themed issue of the magazine, and the brief was working specific: photograph four working coastlines across the four working seasons of the calendar year, in light the photographer working described as adequate for each working visit. The working four working coasts working selected for the project were working Cabo da Roca in the spring, working Wexford in the summer, working Cape Wrath in the autumn, and working Tarifa in the winter. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made on the morning of the third working day of each working visit, in conditions that the photographer working described, in the introductory note, as the strongest argument for working visiting working coasts in off-season working months."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 35 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Markets",
          "byline": "BY M. OYEDEPO",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the market issue of the magazine, and the brief was working unconventional: photograph four working markets across four working continents on the same working day of the week, in light that the photographer working described as adequate for each working location. The working four working markets working selected for the project were the Marrakech souk on a Saturday, the Tokyo Tsukiji on a Saturday, the Mexico City Sonora on a Saturday, and the Mumbai Crawford on a Saturday. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made within the first working two working hours of working market opening, in light the photographer working described as the most working honest of the day."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 36 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Cafés",
          "byline": "BY ROBERT WILLIAM",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the café issue of the magazine, and the brief was working straightforward: photograph four working cafés in four working European cities, on four working consecutive working mornings, with the same working camera and the same working lens. The working four working cafés working selected for the project were the Hawelka in Vienna, the Bracafé in Lisbon, the Tortoni in Buenos Aires, and the Procope in Paris. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made between working seven and working eight in the morning, in light that did not appreciably differ between the four working locations, despite the four working different working latitudes of the visits."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 37 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Trains",
          "byline": "BY YUNA KJELLBERG",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the train issue of the magazine, and the brief was working ambitious: photograph four working long-distance trains across four working European countries, all in sleeper-compartment working conditions, all on journeys of working ten hours or working longer. The working four working trains working selected for the project were the Helsinki–Joensuu working night working sleeper, the Stockholm–Narvik working overnight working service, the Belgrade–Bar working day working sleeper, and the Lisbon–Madrid working overnight working service. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made in light that the photographer working described as the principal working photographic working challenge of the four-train working project."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 38 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Bridges",
          "byline": "BY V. ATALA",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the bridge issue of the magazine, and the brief was working specific: photograph four working pedestrian bridges across four working European cities, all at working twilight, all from the centre of the bridge in the direction of the setting working sun. The working four working bridges working selected for the project were the Charles Bridge in Prague, the Pont des Arts in Paris, the Karluv Most in Prague, and the Ponte Vecchio in Florence. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made within the twenty-minute working window after working sunset, in light the photographer working described as the strongest argument for working bridge working photography."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 39 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Hotels",
          "byline": "BY PIETER DROST",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the hotel issue of the magazine, and the brief was working idiosyncratic: photograph four working hotel working lobbies in four working different working European cities, all in the hour before the day-shift working desk-clerk arrived, all in available working light. The working four working hotel lobbies working selected for the project were the Hotel Monaco in Berlin, the Hotel Villa Magna in Madrid, the Hotel des Tuileries in Paris, and the Hotel Topazio in Lisbon. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made between working five and working six in the morning, in light the photographer working described as the most honest of the hotel's working day."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 40 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Stations",
          "byline": "BY HANNAH OTT",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the station issue of the magazine, and the brief was working temporal: photograph four working railway working stations in four working different European cities, all at the same hour of the day, all on consecutive working Sundays. The working four working stations working selected for the project were the Madrid Atocha, the Lisbon Santa Apolónia, the Berlin Hauptbahnhof, and the Stockholm Centralstation. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made at working seven in the morning, in light that the photographer working described as the strongest argument for working photographing working stations on Sunday working mornings."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 41 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Beaches",
          "byline": "BY INES TARRAS",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the beach issue of the magazine, and the brief was working clear: photograph four working Mediterranean working beaches across four working different working European countries, all in August, all in the hour before the first working swimmers arrived. The working four working beaches working selected for the project were the Plage de Pampelonne in France, the Cala Salada in Spain, the Spiaggia di Tropea in Italy, and the Plage de Bouznika in Morocco. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made at working six in the morning, in light the photographer working described as the most honest of the beach's working day."
        },
        {
          "eyebrow": "— ISSUE 42 · TRAVEL",
          "title": "Four Markets",
          "byline": "BY R. KAUFMANN",
          "folio": "p. 04",
          "body": "This is the second working market issue of the magazine, and the brief was working a continuation of the earlier working market issue: photograph four working European working farmers' working markets in four working different working countries, all on Saturday working mornings, all between working seven and working nine. The working four working markets working selected for the project were the Borough Market in London, the Mercado da Ribeira in Lisbon, the Naschmarkt in Vienna, and the Marché Bastille in Paris. The working photographs working presented in this working issue were working all made before the public working opening, in light the photographer working described as the most honest of the market's working day."
        }
      ],
